HEADWORD: Cnidaria
<hw>Cni*da"ri*a</hw> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧*d⟦amac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See <er>Cnida</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A comprehensive group equivalent to the true
C⟦oe⟧lenterata, <it>i. e.</it>, exclusive of the sponges. They are so
named from presence of stinging cells (<part>cnidae</part>) in the
tissues. See <er>Coelenterata</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cnidoblast</ent>⟦br⟧
